We would like to use the notion of 'global property substitution' in Confluence, as in adding a file in standard Java properties format which can then be used to fill in values when referenced in the Confluence installation...which means that we'd only have to change the value in the properties file to get the correct value in the rendered content. I see the User Macros functionality, but some on my team have asked for the ability just to deploy a simple .properties file to provide value substitution. It'd be nice to be able to edit said properties file through the standard administration pages in Confluence. Does the functionality exist? I've looked through the plugins and base docs and nothing seems to exactly fit the bill.

Ex.

our_props.properties
url.svn=http://myserver/svn/mainrepo
url.dev_admin=http://devserver/admin

Page1
To check out our internal projects, see {props:url.svn}

Page2
To administer our development server, see {props:url.dev_admin}

