It seems wasteful to default the Location field on the Edit Page screen to "open", especially on instances of Confluence with lots of spaces/pages, because it increases the page height significantly and obscures the fields below it (restrictions, labels). Also, I don't think typical use involves moving the page around more than once or twice after initial creation. Perhaps the field can default to "open" when *adding* a page, and "closed" when *editing*? I would also settle for a user preference (cookie) that remembers which you prefer (like the Add Comment field in JIRA issues), but that's probably a little overkill.

