Dynamictasklist version 1 macro produces error message when it is used in space template. Steps to reproduce:
# Go to: any space -> Browse Space -> Advance -> Templates.
# Create new template with the following:
{noformat}
{dynamictasklist: test}
{noformat}
# Click Preview button.

[Form field markup for templates|http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Form+Field+Markup+for+Template] does not work with special characters, such as:  -, &, %, $. The steps to reproduce:

Create the following code in a page:
{noformat}
@team|list(A&team,B_team)@
{noformat}
The dropdown box is not created.

The following markup, with ampersand changed to an underscore works correctly.
{noformat}
@team|list(A_team,B_team)@
{noformat}

Other special characters that cannot be used include 
{noformat}
/ * , \ - % $ 
{noformat}

