Case in point, the \{cache} macro can't work if the content contained within it does a #requiresResource, as it can't reproduce that call when displaying the cached content:

http://developer.atlassian.com/jira/browse/CACHE-16

Not sure how best to fix this. Maybe find a way to divert all requireresource calls to the RenderContext if they're performed in the course of macro execution?

